Alternate-skyculture asterism data (data/asterisms/*.json, excluding
western.json) is derived from the Stellarium project's skyculture dataset
(https://github.com/Stellarium/stellarium/tree/master/skycultures). Each
included culture is normalized from its upstream index.json into the
planisphere's polyline-of-HIP-ids format by scripts/build-asterisms.mjs;
data is not hand-edited.

- data/asterisms/chinese.json — from skycultures/chinese, licensed under
  Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC-BY-SA 4.0).
  Original authors: Karrie Berglund (Digitalis Education Solutions), Sun
  Shuwei. Source references include Yi Shitong, "Chinese and Western
  Contrast Star Chart and Catalogue 1950.0" (Beijing: Science Press, 1981)
  and the imperial-era "Complete Studies of Astronomical" (儀象考成, 1756).

- data/asterisms/indian.json — from skycultures/indian, licensed under
  CC-BY-SA 4.0. Original authors: Tanmoy Saha and contributors from the
  sanskrit-coders community (https://github.com/sanskrit-coders), notably
  Vishvas Vasuki. Represents the Vedic / Nakshatra sky.

- data/asterisms/norse_edda.json — from skycultures/norse_edda, licensed
  under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY 4.0).
  Original author: Jakob Eyermann, consulting with Susanne M. Hoffmann,
  with constellations partly drawn from Jonas Persson's "Norse" sky
  culture. Reconstructs Germanic/Norse asterisms from the Poetic and
  Prose Eddas and related sources.

- data/asterisms/hawaiian_starlines.json — from
  skycultures/hawaiian_starlines, licensed under CC-BY-SA 4.0. Master
  navigator: Mau Piailug of Satawal, passed to Nainoa Thompson; sky
  culture contributed in 2017 by Darren Kamalu, Christopher Blake, and
  students of Kamehameha Schools Kapalama (Honolulu, Hawai'i) — Jonah
  Apo, Nicholas Koanui, Brenden Aila, and the Celestial Navigation class.
  Used for Polynesian voyaging aboard Hōkūle'a.

- data/asterisms/maori.json — from skycultures/maori, licensed under
  CC-BY-SA 4.0. Original author: Dan Smale. Covers a small set of
  traditional Māori whānau o ngā whetū (star groupings).

The Western asterism set (data/asterisms/western.json) mirrors the
stick-figure lines from data/constellations.json (Stellarium modern_st,
public domain) and is provided as a selectable skyculture in the same
bundled format as the Stellarium-derived sets.
